ccumulation of soil NO3 - on manure plots. Nitrate accumulation was greater in the dry year 2003 due to reduced leaching and decreased N2O loss. Most NH4 + was retained in the 0-10 cm layer and only NO3 - moved into the lower soil layer. The organic manure treatments did not result in increased grass productivity but did result in higher contents of soil mineral N (NH4 + and NO3 -), increased soil and plant total N content and resulted in an overall higher loss of N2O compared to mineral fertilisers. ?? 2006 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.},
